WEBVTT

00:00.626 --> 00:02.461
Previously on
"Promised Land"....

00:02.461 --> 00:04.171
I took the little vineyard
and turned it into

00:04.171 --> 00:05.964
one of the largest wine
producers in the country.

00:05.964 --> 00:08.800
Well, if I ever let it slip
Joe Sandoval is a fiction...

00:09.676 --> 00:11.803
I'm not the only one
who's undocumented.

00:11.803 --> 00:14.681
Are you willing to blow up
your mother's life?

00:14.681 --> 00:16.683
I'm Margaret.

00:16.683 --> 00:19.061
I'm only the mother
to three of your kids.

00:19.061 --> 00:20.229
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

00:20.229 --> 00:22.731
Just hearing "Carlos Rincón"
gave Joe a start.

00:22.731 --> 00:25.067
Let's find out
who Carlos Rincón is.

00:25.067 --> 00:26.151
"Man got hit by a car."

00:26.151 --> 00:27.236
[ Thud ]
[ Gasps ]

00:27.236 --> 00:28.237
[ Tires squeal ]

00:28.237 --> 00:29.905
I know it was you.

00:31.198 --> 00:35.077
♪ Our own party,
stick together like glitter ♪

00:35.077 --> 00:36.828
Michael: Look,
I'm just saying that

00:36.828 --> 00:39.581
considering this pitch is
for the Heritage House board,

00:39.581 --> 00:40.916
pink might be
a little too ‐‐

00:40.916 --> 00:44.336
Oh, don't be a boomer and say
pink is too feminine, Michael.

00:44.336 --> 00:45.379
Come on.

00:45.379 --> 00:46.672
Boomer?

00:46.672 --> 00:48.131
How old do you
think I am?

00:48.131 --> 00:51.385
Well, you're married to my
sister, so you must be ancient.

00:51.385 --> 00:53.262
Check it out.

00:53.262 --> 00:54.846
What do you think?

00:54.846 --> 00:56.640
Oh.

00:56.640 --> 00:59.017
Well? On a shelf full
of dark bottles?

00:59.017 --> 01:01.019
This is really good,
Carmen.

01:01.019 --> 01:02.187
[ Chuckles ]

01:02.187 --> 01:04.231
[ Cellphone chimes ]

01:04.231 --> 01:05.524
Pick it up tomorrow?

01:05.524 --> 01:07.568
A marketing recruiter
saw my work on Insta,

01:07.568 --> 01:09.069
and they want to
have lunch with me.

01:09.069 --> 01:11.154
Oh. Wow.
Yeah.

01:11.154 --> 01:12.823
I'm glad someone
appreciates your talent,

01:12.823 --> 01:17.119
'cause I got to say,
nobody in your family seems to.

01:17.119 --> 01:19.413
Mm. Not nobody.

01:19.413 --> 01:21.415
♪ What can we do now? ♪

01:21.415 --> 01:23.834
See ya.

01:23.834 --> 01:26.044
Yeah.

01:27.129 --> 01:30.382
I'm here to meet Margaux?
With an "X".

01:30.382 --> 01:33.719
Sorry. I don't know why
I spelled that out for you.

01:36.013 --> 01:37.723
Thank you.

01:37.723 --> 01:39.224
Hello, Carmen.

01:41.310 --> 01:42.769
Mom?

01:46.106 --> 01:47.274
[ Bell tolls ]

01:47.274 --> 01:49.109
Are those our
new uniforms?

01:49.109 --> 01:50.610
Uh, maybe.

01:50.610 --> 01:52.112
This one right here
is number 9,

01:52.112 --> 01:54.072
the striker's number,
so definitely not you.

01:54.072 --> 01:55.782
That's me! I can score goals.
You know that.

01:55.782 --> 01:56.908
I don't think you can.

01:56.908 --> 02:00.120
This is so good for him.
So good.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.789
It's good to be needed.
Gives him a sense of purpose.

02:02.789 --> 02:04.041
Right?

02:04.041 --> 02:05.417
You know,
I should get going.

02:05.417 --> 02:07.502
My ESL class
is about to start.

02:07.502 --> 02:08.920
You're not nervous?

02:08.920 --> 02:12.215
Well, haven't
taught in years.

02:12.215 --> 02:13.550
You taught me.

02:14.718 --> 02:17.638
Yeah.
You were a good student.

02:19.389 --> 02:21.224
Better than most.

02:23.935 --> 02:26.104
"He went to see a mov‐‐"

02:26.104 --> 02:28.982
Unh‐unh.
"Movie."

02:33.570 --> 02:36.365
It's time to eat.

02:36.365 --> 02:39.660
There they are!
What a fine‐looking crew.

02:39.660 --> 02:42.829
I hope you're all hungry.
Beautiful.

02:44.623 --> 02:48.377
Ladies and gentlemen,
today we eat together,

02:48.377 --> 02:50.712
as a thank‐you
for all your hard work.

02:50.712 --> 02:53.131
I'd especially like to thank
my foreman, Gonzo,

02:53.131 --> 02:57.094
who always finds
the best workers in Sonoma.

02:57.094 --> 02:59.930
[ Cheering ]
Gonzito!

02:59.930 --> 03:02.974
Heritage House bottles
may have my stamp on them,

03:02.974 --> 03:06.353
but this is a family winery,
and I consider you all family,

03:06.353 --> 03:08.021
so let's eat.

03:08.021 --> 03:09.147
‐iSalud!
‐iSalud!

03:09.147 --> 03:11.191
[ Glasses clinking ]
Salud.

03:11.191 --> 03:12.859
I like
this pinot, Daddy.

03:12.859 --> 03:15.195
The blend tastes lighter.
The rainy season?

03:15.195 --> 03:17.280
Very good, Margaret.

03:17.280 --> 03:20.283
Anyone else have thoughts
about this vintage?

03:22.411 --> 03:24.287
Mm! Mm!

03:24.287 --> 03:30.127
I think this wine is
sweet, earthy, and tasty!

03:30.127 --> 03:32.921
[ Laughter ]

03:32.921 --> 03:35.173
Tasty.
[ Chuckles ]

03:35.173 --> 03:36.633
What about you?

03:36.633 --> 03:38.343
♪♪

03:38.343 --> 03:41.221
Any thoughts on this vintage?

03:48.437 --> 03:50.147
[ Speaks Spanish ]

03:54.359 --> 03:55.402
What did he say?

03:55.402 --> 03:59.781
"First it tastes sweet,
like a kiss."

04:02.325 --> 04:04.286
[ Speaks Spanish ]

04:10.417 --> 04:12.836
[ Light laughter ]

04:12.836 --> 04:15.338
"Then the grape
kisses you back."

04:15.338 --> 04:16.715
Well, I'll be damned.

04:18.091 --> 04:19.759
Couldn't have said it
better myself.

04:19.759 --> 04:21.344
[ Laughs ]

04:22.554 --> 04:23.972
What's your name, son?

04:23.972 --> 04:25.432
Uh...

04:25.432 --> 04:28.602
His name is Joe.
Joe Sandoval.

04:28.602 --> 04:32.397
Joe. Salud.

04:32.397 --> 04:34.024
Salud.

04:34.024 --> 04:35.942
‐iSalud!
‐iSalud!

04:48.079 --> 04:49.247
Five minutes, Lettie.

04:49.247 --> 04:50.957
[ Speaks Spanish ]

04:52.125 --> 04:53.251
Rosa?

04:53.251 --> 04:54.252
Juana?

05:30.747 --> 05:32.457
[ Dial tone ]

05:41.383 --> 05:42.926
Veronica: 'Cause I think if
you say I'm right...

05:42.926 --> 05:44.469
Yeah.
...then that means you're what?

05:44.469 --> 05:45.804
What? Nothing.
I'm right, as well.
Joe: Ah, good timing.

05:45.804 --> 05:48.390
I'm right.
Veronica, Antonio.

05:48.390 --> 05:50.058
You remember Javi Soto.

05:50.058 --> 05:52.477
Gonzo's son. Of course.
Hi. How you doing?

05:52.477 --> 05:53.770
I'm good, thanks.

05:53.770 --> 05:56.523
You're going to be seeing
a lot more of Javier.

05:56.523 --> 05:58.483
I've brought him on
as our new GM.

05:58.483 --> 06:00.110
Our new GM?

06:00.110 --> 06:01.403
You don't think you
should have mentioned it?

06:01.403 --> 06:03.029
I mentioned it.
Didn't I mention it?

06:03.029 --> 06:06.116
Ah, well, Javier's been
working over in Coombsville.

06:06.116 --> 06:08.535
I can't think of a better
replacement for Mateo.

06:08.535 --> 06:10.328
I can.

06:10.328 --> 06:11.872
Got a stack of résumés
sitting on my desk.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.293
Excuse my eldest son.

06:16.293 --> 06:19.296
Apparently he left his manners
in New York.

06:19.296 --> 06:20.922
Javier grew up
on this vineyard.

06:20.922 --> 06:22.132
He knows this place
better than I do.

06:22.132 --> 06:24.426
Javier: Hey, hey, Joe,
it's okay.

06:24.426 --> 06:25.760
It sounds like this came
as a surprise.

06:25.760 --> 06:28.972
Uh, there's a big shipment
of barrels coming in.

06:28.972 --> 06:30.265
I should go supervise.

06:33.226 --> 06:34.311
What the hell was that?

06:34.311 --> 06:35.812
You're sidestepping us.

06:35.812 --> 06:37.272
That man went from
working in the dirt

06:37.272 --> 06:39.232
to working at a desk
in Coombsville.

06:39.232 --> 06:40.984
I know you know that's not easy
for a brown man.

06:40.984 --> 06:42.819
Yeah, no one's questioning
his résumé, Pa.

06:42.819 --> 06:44.029
I am.

06:44.029 --> 06:45.780
Okay.

06:45.780 --> 06:49.367
Clearly, this was just
a miscommunication, yeah?

06:49.367 --> 06:51.828
Veronica,
you're the new CEO.

06:51.828 --> 06:53.413
Stand up for yourself
more than I'm standing up

06:53.413 --> 06:54.789
for you right now.

06:54.789 --> 06:58.627
♪♪

06:58.627 --> 07:01.212
I haven't seen you
since you were...

07:01.212 --> 07:02.964
16, I think?

07:02.964 --> 07:04.716
You're even lovelier
than ever.

07:04.716 --> 07:06.593
You did this just to
have lunch with me.

07:06.593 --> 07:08.720
Next time,
do what you usually do ‐‐

07:08.720 --> 07:10.889
send a generic postcard
from one of your hotels.

07:10.889 --> 07:12.641
Okay, I deserve that.

07:17.187 --> 07:18.855
[ Sighs ]

07:21.775 --> 07:24.444
Just please sit
and listen.

07:30.158 --> 07:32.619
I think you're very talented,
Carmen.

07:32.619 --> 07:35.789
I showed your work to my
marketing team, and they agree.

07:35.789 --> 07:37.040
So much so,
they'd like to see

07:37.040 --> 07:38.458
the rest of
your portfolio ‐‐

07:38.458 --> 07:41.086
see if you make sense
for Taste of Sonoma.

07:41.086 --> 07:42.962
My hotel is
hosting this year.

07:42.962 --> 07:44.214
Okay.

07:44.214 --> 07:47.926
And you'll be happy to know
this job pays very well.

07:47.926 --> 07:51.179
I don't care about the money.
I just want respect.

07:51.179 --> 07:53.264
I get that.

07:53.264 --> 07:56.101
My father didn't think
a woman could run a vineyard.

07:56.101 --> 07:58.269
And I was proud
to prove him wrong.

07:58.269 --> 08:00.605
But then you lost
the vineyard to my father.

08:00.605 --> 08:03.942
And then I lost your father
to my best friend.

08:03.942 --> 08:05.610
Lettie.

08:05.610 --> 08:07.529
Joe always loved Lettie,

08:07.529 --> 08:10.323
even when she was married
to your Uncle Billy,

08:10.323 --> 08:14.994
and when I realized that
was never going to change,

08:14.994 --> 08:18.498
I told him to buy me out
of the vineyard.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.333
I took that money,
I went to Europe.

08:20.333 --> 08:22.460
People said I couldn't
start a luxury hotel.

08:22.460 --> 08:26.131
I was happy to prove
them wrong, too...

08:26.131 --> 08:27.716
but at a cost.

08:29.217 --> 08:32.470
I'm a stranger to
my own children.

08:34.264 --> 08:37.767
No offense,
but if this is your apology,

08:37.767 --> 08:39.519
it needs work.

08:39.519 --> 08:43.815
I'm not asking for
your forgiveness, Carmen.

08:43.815 --> 08:46.276
Just your understanding.

08:46.276 --> 08:49.487
I can't imagine
how my leaving...

08:49.487 --> 08:52.032
must have affected
you kids,

08:52.032 --> 08:54.576
but I knew Lettie
would raise you well,

08:54.576 --> 08:58.121
and at the time, I thought...
better than I would.

09:05.336 --> 09:07.422
I'm sending you
my portfolio.

09:10.008 --> 09:12.135
Been wondering...

09:12.135 --> 09:13.720
who else knows?

09:14.345 --> 09:15.847
What do you mean?

09:15.847 --> 09:18.349
Who else knows
about you?

09:18.349 --> 09:19.350
That you sleep with men.

09:19.350 --> 09:20.351
[ Scoffs ]

09:23.521 --> 09:25.565
If you're trying
to embarrass me...

09:25.565 --> 09:26.566
Flaco knows.

09:26.566 --> 09:28.526
And to answer
your question,

09:28.526 --> 09:30.820
I don't advertise
who I have sex with.

09:30.820 --> 09:31.905
[ Chuckles ]

09:31.905 --> 09:33.114
I don't hide it, either.

09:33.114 --> 09:35.283
Oh, how convenient.

09:37.118 --> 09:38.870
Does your father know?

09:40.080 --> 09:42.082
Yeah.

09:42.082 --> 09:44.209
Better late than never,
huh?

09:44.209 --> 09:45.835
I never meant
to hurt you.

09:45.835 --> 09:47.837
No, you didn't hurt me.
We had a deal.

09:47.837 --> 09:51.091
We were 18.
We had a deal, Javier.

09:51.091 --> 09:53.093
We'd go home, we'd tell
our families, and then ‐‐

09:53.093 --> 09:54.469
And then what?

09:54.469 --> 09:57.305
What, we'd live
happily ever after?

09:57.305 --> 10:00.475
I held up my end.
I told Joe.

10:00.475 --> 10:01.935
You know how he reacted?
Huh?

10:01.935 --> 10:03.645
I'm sure it was unpleasant.
No, unpleasant?

10:03.645 --> 10:05.188
Yes, unpleasant, Antonio.

10:05.188 --> 10:06.773
Probably yelled at you?
Oh.

10:06.773 --> 10:08.274
Called you mariposa?
Okay.

10:08.274 --> 10:11.111
Then he sent you off
to Harvard and flew you
home for Christmas...

10:11.111 --> 10:13.279
Oh, please, please.
...which I'm sure made for
a very unpleasant Christmas ‐‐

10:13.279 --> 10:16.366
You have no idea
what he put me through!
You want to know what my father
would have done?

10:16.366 --> 10:18.243
How badly he would have
beaten me?

10:20.745 --> 10:25.208
I had to wait years
to come out to my family.

10:25.208 --> 10:27.418
I had to wait till I could
kick my father's ass.

10:29.838 --> 10:32.841
And on the day I told him,
I did.

10:32.841 --> 10:35.343
My father who I love.

10:38.555 --> 10:40.431
Look, I'm sorry that
I broke our deal

10:40.431 --> 10:42.642
and that I got scared.

10:42.642 --> 10:49.858
♪♪

10:49.858 --> 10:51.526
Get in.

10:52.652 --> 10:55.446
The day
I told my father,

10:55.446 --> 10:57.323
he said,
"Sleep with whoever you want.

10:57.323 --> 10:59.033
Just keep it hidden."

10:59.033 --> 11:01.327
For a while,
I tried to play the part.

11:02.787 --> 11:04.497
In Joe's eyes,
it was over.

11:04.497 --> 11:07.041
I'd never be
head of this company ‐‐

11:07.041 --> 11:08.710
the one thing
I always wanted.

11:08.710 --> 11:11.296
I know your path
wasn't easy.

11:12.964 --> 11:15.592
But mine was more than
just unpleasant.

11:20.638 --> 11:22.765
So you brought me all the way
out here just to tell me that?

11:22.765 --> 11:26.227
No. I brought you out here
because I need your help.

11:27.187 --> 11:29.022
You know this place
as well as my father does.

11:29.022 --> 11:30.523
He said so himself.

11:30.523 --> 11:33.693
I need you to tell me
everything you know...

11:33.693 --> 11:35.737
about this.

11:35.737 --> 11:42.285
♪♪

11:52.545 --> 11:54.505
Yes, I have the truck part.

11:56.883 --> 11:58.676
Excuse me,
Mr. Honeycroft?

11:58.676 --> 11:59.677
I talk to you
five minutes?

11:59.677 --> 12:00.720
You've got two.

12:01.846 --> 12:03.681
[ Speaks Spanish ]

12:03.681 --> 12:06.517
His ‐‐ His mother
is very sick.

12:06.517 --> 12:09.062
[ Speaks Spanish ]

12:13.608 --> 12:15.777
Because you said
that we are family...

12:15.777 --> 12:18.196
[ Speaks Spanish ]

12:21.366 --> 12:24.160
Because you are a very rich
and generous man...

12:24.160 --> 12:26.829
[ Speaks Spanish ]

12:31.417 --> 12:34.337
If you could borrow him
$5,000.

12:34.337 --> 12:37.548
I pay you back total, señor.
I promise. Total.

12:39.717 --> 12:42.720
Took a lot of guts
to ask that.

12:42.720 --> 12:45.223
But, um, if I gave you
that money,

12:45.223 --> 12:48.685
I'd have every Juan, Luis,
and Jose asking the same.

12:48.685 --> 12:50.061
Sorry, kid.

12:51.396 --> 12:52.981
Come.

12:52.981 --> 13:02.991
♪♪

13:02.991 --> 13:04.492
Gracias, Joe.

13:07.412 --> 13:10.123
Ann: Veronica.
Wonderful to see you.

13:10.123 --> 13:12.959
Have a seat.
I'll just pull up your accounts.

13:13.918 --> 13:15.753
What's new
in your world?

13:15.753 --> 13:17.505
You know, same old.

13:17.505 --> 13:19.465
We make the wine,
they drink it.

13:19.465 --> 13:21.551
I love to hear that.

13:21.551 --> 13:23.261
So, um,
I got your text.

13:23.261 --> 13:25.054
$50,000 is
a sizeable withdrawal.

13:25.054 --> 13:27.056
May I ask
what it's for?

13:27.056 --> 13:28.474
[ Thud ]

13:28.474 --> 13:30.268
[ Monitor beeping ]

13:30.727 --> 13:35.315
Yeah, I'm, uh, surprising
Michael with a dive trip.

13:35.315 --> 13:37.650
It's ‐‐ The charter requires
a large cash deposit.

13:37.650 --> 13:38.693
You know how it is.

13:38.693 --> 13:40.653
He's a lucky guy.
Yeah.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.323
You wanted this pulled from
the ancillary account, correct?

13:44.323 --> 13:47.160
Yeah.
Is there an issue?

13:47.160 --> 13:49.579
It's just...there are
no funds in that account.

13:49.579 --> 13:51.080
They've all been
withdrawn.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.249
Wait, what do you mean?
By who?

13:53.249 --> 13:54.250
[ Typing ]

13:54.250 --> 13:55.460
By Michael.

13:55.460 --> 13:57.378
By my Michael?

13:57.378 --> 14:00.214
Did he not tell you?

14:00.214 --> 14:02.383
There was a hiccup at the bank.

14:02.383 --> 14:03.468
Yeah, well, I'm sorry.

14:03.468 --> 14:05.720
I don't exactly carry
$50,000 on me.

14:05.720 --> 14:07.555
He's testing me.

14:07.555 --> 14:08.806
You know that's what
he's doing, right?

14:08.806 --> 14:10.141
I have to go.

14:10.141 --> 14:12.226
Antonio, I don't think
that's what's happening here.

14:12.226 --> 14:13.770
You and Javier ended
a long time ago.

14:13.770 --> 14:15.688
How would Pa even know?

14:18.691 --> 14:20.526
Why would I ever tell him
about you guys?

14:20.526 --> 14:23.488
Maybe for the same reasons you
"didn't support me" when I left.

14:23.488 --> 14:24.489
Those were your words.

14:24.489 --> 14:26.074
You think that
was intentional?

14:29.410 --> 14:32.246
I was first in line
to be head of this company,

14:32.246 --> 14:33.790
and then I came out,

14:33.790 --> 14:37.585
and suddenly, the same meetings
I got excluded from,

14:37.585 --> 14:39.462
you started getting
invited to.

14:39.462 --> 14:42.215
You think you should be
sitting in my seat?

14:44.217 --> 14:46.427
You think you should be
CEO of this company?

14:50.139 --> 14:51.933
'Tonio, don't let
him do this.

14:51.933 --> 14:54.393
Don't let him divide us.

14:54.393 --> 14:56.187
Come on.

14:56.187 --> 15:00.483
You know I'll have your back,
even when Pa doesn't.

15:00.483 --> 15:02.443
Daniela: This is
how you crush grapes?

15:02.443 --> 15:05.279
I thought that there
would be a machine.

15:05.279 --> 15:08.616
This is how people have been
doing it for 6,000 years.

15:08.616 --> 15:09.992
It was good enough
for the Greeks.

15:09.992 --> 15:12.286
Do you want to try?

15:12.286 --> 15:14.455
♪ It's got me open wide ♪

15:14.455 --> 15:17.500
So my family's having
dinner tonight.

15:17.500 --> 15:18.876
You should come.

15:18.876 --> 15:22.130
It's a family dinner,
Mateo.

15:22.130 --> 15:24.215
They don't want me there.

15:24.215 --> 15:25.716
That's not true,
and even if it is, who cares?

15:25.716 --> 15:26.926
I want you there.

15:26.926 --> 15:28.886
You should have seen the look
your mother gave me

15:28.886 --> 15:30.888
when I told her
I was staying here.

15:30.888 --> 15:32.473
I don't want
anyone to think

15:32.473 --> 15:34.725
that I'm taking
advantage of you.

15:34.725 --> 15:38.229
I mean, as you can see,
I need an extra set of hands.

15:38.229 --> 15:39.438
[ Chuckles ]

15:39.438 --> 15:40.898
Besides,
I'm the one getting a deal.

15:40.898 --> 15:42.275
You get a place to stay,

15:42.275 --> 15:44.277
but I get the best coffee
in the world every morning.

15:44.277 --> 15:45.778
It's instant coffee.

15:45.778 --> 15:47.780
[ Both laugh ]

15:47.780 --> 15:49.740
Come on.
What do you say?

15:49.740 --> 15:51.534
Come with me.

15:51.534 --> 15:53.870
I can't tonight.

15:53.870 --> 15:56.455
I promised my family
I would call them.

15:59.792 --> 16:01.085
I'll make you a deal.

16:01.085 --> 16:03.337
You make me
coffee tomorrow,

16:03.337 --> 16:05.840
and I will come to
your next family dinner.

16:05.840 --> 16:08.426
[ Chuckles ]

16:08.426 --> 16:09.927
It's a deal.

16:12.054 --> 16:14.348
So, uh, I went
to the bank today.

16:14.348 --> 16:16.517
Anything you want
to say?

16:16.517 --> 16:17.894
[ Laughs ] Not really.

16:17.894 --> 16:20.021
I mean, I needed to
buy some video equipment.

16:20.021 --> 16:22.940
$50,000 worth
of video equipment?

16:22.940 --> 16:25.067
I pitch
Silicon Valley companies, V.

16:25.067 --> 16:27.486
I mean, come on. I can't walk
in there with a tablet.

16:27.486 --> 16:29.655
No, of course not.
Were you planning on telling me?

16:29.655 --> 16:31.616
I'd like to think that
I don't have to.

16:31.616 --> 16:33.743
I'd like to think that
my wife would trust me.

16:33.743 --> 16:35.661
[ Scoffs ]
But since we're on
the subject, though, V,

16:35.661 --> 16:37.288
what did you need
the money for?

16:37.288 --> 16:38.497
That's my business.

16:38.497 --> 16:39.665
And why is that?

16:39.665 --> 16:42.418
It's simple, Michael.
It was my money.

16:44.921 --> 16:47.089
Joe: Marta,
you outdid yourself.

16:47.089 --> 16:48.424
Marta: You say that
every time, jefe.

16:48.424 --> 16:50.051
And I mean it
every time.

16:50.051 --> 16:54.138
♪♪

16:54.138 --> 16:55.681
Junior,
how's the knee?

16:55.681 --> 16:57.225
Junior: Physical therapy's
going okay.

16:57.225 --> 16:59.769
I'm having a lot of fun coaching
these underprivileged kids.

16:59.769 --> 17:01.562
Father Ramos
put me up to it.

17:01.562 --> 17:02.730
You like this guy,
huh?

17:02.730 --> 17:04.815
Yeah.
Yeah, all the kids love him.

17:04.815 --> 17:07.318
It's just tough. They don't have
money for cleats or anything.

17:07.318 --> 17:09.195
Well, keep it up.
I'm proud of you.

17:09.195 --> 17:13.032
So who else wants to
share something about their day?

17:13.032 --> 17:14.492
Carmen, how about you?

17:14.492 --> 17:16.702
Not much. Saw Mom.

17:20.122 --> 17:21.415
Who'd you see?

17:21.415 --> 17:23.709
Your mother is sitting
right next to you.

17:23.709 --> 17:27.004
Not like that.
I meant...Margaret.

17:27.004 --> 17:28.798
It's okay, cariño.
I know what you meant.

17:28.798 --> 17:30.258
Why on Earth would you want
to talk to her?

17:30.258 --> 17:32.552
Her hotel is hosting
the Taste of Sonoma,

17:32.552 --> 17:35.346
and she's putting me up
to do the marketing materials.

17:35.346 --> 17:37.723
Listen, that woman's
using you against me.

17:37.723 --> 17:39.850
I want you to
stay away from her.

17:39.850 --> 17:41.394
No.

17:41.394 --> 17:42.687
What did you say?

17:42.687 --> 17:45.064
I said no.

17:45.064 --> 17:46.482
You call it "using me."

17:46.482 --> 17:48.359
I call it giving me
an opportunity,

17:48.359 --> 17:51.237
and that's more
than Heritage House
has ever given me.

17:51.237 --> 17:52.780
Okay, that's not fair,
Carmen.

17:52.780 --> 17:54.240
Yes, it is.

17:55.700 --> 17:58.160
Joe,
I completely understand

17:58.160 --> 18:00.997
why Carmen would want to have a
relationship with her mother ‐‐

18:00.997 --> 18:02.999
at least
get to know her.

18:02.999 --> 18:04.542
Gracias, Mami.

18:04.542 --> 18:05.710
And I mean, who knows?

18:05.710 --> 18:08.045
It's been a long time
since we all knew Margaret.

18:08.045 --> 18:12.091
Maybe ‐‐
Maybe she's changed.

18:21.225 --> 18:22.351
[ Speaks Spanish ]

18:23.519 --> 18:25.021
Gonzo: iOye!

18:26.772 --> 18:28.274
iOye!

19:06.729 --> 19:07.772
Hey.

19:30.002 --> 19:31.295
What's his problem,
huh?

19:44.225 --> 19:45.601
Okay?

19:50.189 --> 19:52.108
Wayne: Always good
to see you, Joe.

19:52.108 --> 19:54.527
I hope you guys won't mind
if I get down to business.

19:54.527 --> 19:56.487
I heard the Alliance
is holding this year's

19:56.487 --> 19:59.615
Taste of Sonoma event
at the Honeycroft Hotel.

19:59.615 --> 20:01.742
I'd like to think I would
have gotten a heads up,

20:01.742 --> 20:03.828
in light of everything I have
done for the Alliance

20:03.828 --> 20:05.037
over the years.

20:05.037 --> 20:07.707
Be that as it may,
Margaret Honeycroft

20:07.707 --> 20:10.584
has launched a hostile
takeover of my company.

20:10.584 --> 20:13.003
I'd say that makes her unfit
to hold this year's event.

20:13.003 --> 20:15.339
Joe,
with all due respect,

20:15.339 --> 20:16.966
the Honeycrofts have
lived in this valley

20:16.966 --> 20:19.844
since long before the Sandovals
ever stepped on to a vineyard.

20:19.844 --> 20:22.805
I mean, your people may have
elevated Heritage House,

20:22.805 --> 20:25.683
but the Honeycrofts
elevated Sonoma.

20:31.230 --> 20:36.652
♪♪

20:36.652 --> 20:42.074
♪♪

20:42.074 --> 20:44.118
"My people."

20:44.118 --> 20:45.745
Ron: Why all
the Honeycroft hate, Joe?

20:45.745 --> 20:47.997
Old Oscar was
pretty good to you.

20:47.997 --> 20:50.541
Married you off to his daughter,
made you GM,

20:50.541 --> 20:52.376
and then had
the bad fortune

20:52.376 --> 20:54.962
to drive his car
into the Oro Blanco River,

20:54.962 --> 20:56.964
allowing you to take over
Heritage House.

20:56.964 --> 20:59.091
They never did find his body,
did they, Joe?

20:59.091 --> 21:01.385
I have been hearing
those whispers for years.

21:01.385 --> 21:03.512
I won't dignify them
with a response.

21:03.512 --> 21:05.055
I'll leave it at this.

21:05.055 --> 21:06.682
If you don't move
this year's event,

21:06.682 --> 21:11.228
I will cut my prices so low,
you will be forced to cut yours.

21:11.228 --> 21:12.229
A price war?

21:12.229 --> 21:14.273
Which, given my superior
market position,

21:14.273 --> 21:16.901
I can withstand a hell of a lot
better than you can.

21:16.901 --> 21:18.903
You would cost yourself
millions of dollars

21:18.903 --> 21:20.780
just to hurt us.

21:20.780 --> 21:22.031
He's bluffing.

21:22.031 --> 21:23.699
Try me.

21:23.699 --> 21:25.409
Gentlemen.

21:27.328 --> 21:29.163
Raúl.
Señor.

21:29.163 --> 21:30.748
Gracias.

21:30.748 --> 21:31.916
[ Speaks Spanish ]

21:31.916 --> 21:33.459
She's a beauty.

21:33.459 --> 21:36.003
Ah. That's not even
her good side.

21:47.598 --> 21:49.099
Hey, I think
I told you boys,

21:49.099 --> 21:51.560
English when you're
on the job.

21:51.560 --> 21:54.438
Joe. I'm so sorry.
I was, uh ‐‐

21:54.438 --> 21:55.564
You surprised me.

21:55.564 --> 21:56.941
Joe: That's okay, Wayne.

21:56.941 --> 21:59.568
Your people never
surprise me.

22:03.489 --> 22:04.698
[ Engine revs ]

22:04.698 --> 22:09.370
♪ Con dinero y sin dinero ♪

22:09.370 --> 22:12.623
♪ Hago siempre lo que quiero ♪

22:12.623 --> 22:19.004
♪♪

22:19.004 --> 22:25.469
♪♪

22:25.469 --> 22:27.263
Soon enough, girl.

22:32.059 --> 22:33.477
How have you been, Marta?

22:35.354 --> 22:36.397
Oh.

22:36.397 --> 22:39.358
Margaret!

22:39.358 --> 22:41.026
Lettie!
It's been so long.

22:41.026 --> 22:42.903
You look so beautiful.

22:42.903 --> 22:44.196
And so does the house.

22:44.196 --> 22:45.990
Oh, thank you.

22:45.990 --> 22:47.575
I had Marta
make us a pitcher

22:47.575 --> 22:49.368
of the agua fresca
we used to love.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.120
I add vodka
to mine now.

22:51.120 --> 22:52.872
Now I remember
why we're friends.

22:52.872 --> 22:53.914
[ Both laugh ]

22:53.914 --> 22:56.333
Thank you for coming.

22:56.333 --> 22:58.669
I ‐‐ I'll be honest,
I wasn't sure you would.

22:58.669 --> 23:01.005
You know, I just don't want us
to hide from each other.

23:01.005 --> 23:02.631
I'm not hiding, Lettie.

23:02.631 --> 23:04.466
I'd really love for you
to come see the hotel.

23:04.466 --> 23:05.968
I'd love that, yeah.

23:05.968 --> 23:07.928
And I'm so happy
for your success.

23:07.928 --> 23:10.097
And I think what you're doing
for Carmen is great.

23:10.097 --> 23:11.724
Such a talented girl.

23:11.724 --> 23:13.183
A talented woman.

23:13.183 --> 23:15.519
Yeah, but I'm ‐‐ I'm thinking of
the girl right now, you know?

23:15.519 --> 23:17.855
The ‐‐ The girl who
puts it all out there

23:17.855 --> 23:20.357
and then gets hurt
too easily.

23:20.357 --> 23:22.234
The girl I raised.

23:22.234 --> 23:23.652
Or maybe if Carmen
gets hurt too easily,

23:23.652 --> 23:24.737
you didn't raise
her right.

23:24.737 --> 23:26.322
[ Scoffs ]

23:27.531 --> 23:29.700
I don't know what game
you're playing, Margaret,

23:29.700 --> 23:31.410
but when you and Joe
go to war,

23:31.410 --> 23:32.786
it's usually other people
who get hurt.

23:32.786 --> 23:34.455
That's not gonna
be Carmen.

23:34.455 --> 23:35.623
She's my daughter,
Lettie.

23:35.623 --> 23:37.333
When it's convenient.

23:38.542 --> 23:41.837
Tell me, if you care so much
about Carmen,

23:41.837 --> 23:46.216
why is it that her only real
creative opportunity

23:46.216 --> 23:50.054
has come from me,
not you and Joe?

23:50.054 --> 23:52.765
You really think one job

23:52.765 --> 23:55.309
is gonna make her forget
the fact that you left?

23:55.309 --> 23:56.393
I was pushed out.

23:56.393 --> 23:58.062
You abandoned
your family.

23:58.062 --> 23:59.772
You stole it,

23:59.772 --> 24:03.692
and I was left to rebuild
my life from nothing,

24:03.692 --> 24:05.945
so don't act so innocent
in this, old friend.

24:05.945 --> 24:08.280
Old friend is right.

24:08.280 --> 24:11.450
I will never forget
what you did for me, Margaret,

24:11.450 --> 24:13.327
but I repaid my debt.

24:13.327 --> 24:16.372
I owe you nothing,
and if you hurt my family,

24:16.372 --> 24:19.333
I won't hesitate to let you know
what kind of enemy I can be.

24:19.333 --> 24:20.501
Oh, I remember.

24:23.170 --> 24:25.923
But, Lettie,
you remember this ‐‐

24:25.923 --> 24:28.425
we share our own secret,

24:28.425 --> 24:32.596
so if you try to take me down,
I won't go down alone.

24:35.140 --> 24:36.809
I know my way out.

24:36.809 --> 24:38.394
You always did.

24:38.394 --> 24:45.442
♪♪

24:52.700 --> 24:54.410
Veronica: There was a problem
at the bank.

24:54.410 --> 24:55.869
I need one more day.

24:56.996 --> 24:59.248
You need
another day, huh?

24:59.248 --> 25:01.834
[ Ringing ]
Man: Sonoma County
Sheriff's Department.

25:01.834 --> 25:03.794
Yeah, I've got information
on a hit‐and‐run

25:03.794 --> 25:05.295
that happened
on Route 9.

25:05.295 --> 25:08.507
One moment. I'll transfer you
to the deputy in charge.

25:08.507 --> 25:11.927
I tell them you were the driver,
it's over for you.

25:11.927 --> 25:13.303
You sure about that?

25:13.303 --> 25:15.431
I'm not the one selling
phony work papers.

25:15.431 --> 25:17.349
Look, I don't want
to blow you up.

25:17.349 --> 25:19.101
But I have a family
to feed.

25:19.101 --> 25:21.645
Lam: Deputy Lam.
How can I help you?

25:23.063 --> 25:24.023
[ Beep ]

25:24.023 --> 25:25.524
I'll get you the rest.

25:25.524 --> 25:29.611
♪♪

25:29.611 --> 25:31.780
[ Speaks Spanish ]

25:32.656 --> 25:35.034
Hey, guys.

25:35.034 --> 25:36.326
Hello, uh, Margaret.

25:36.326 --> 25:38.912
Can I steal Joe
for a second?

25:44.877 --> 25:53.385
♪♪

25:53.385 --> 25:55.596
Here, take this.

25:56.930 --> 25:58.432
What? You stole?

25:58.432 --> 25:59.808
No, no, Margaret,
no puedo. I can't ‐‐

25:59.808 --> 26:01.602
He has three more
like it.

26:01.602 --> 26:04.063
Please,
I want you to have it.

26:04.063 --> 26:07.357
No.
Mira, Margaret...

26:08.901 --> 26:11.904
Mi mamá,
she's not sick, okay?

26:11.904 --> 26:14.073
It doesn't matter
what the money's for.

26:14.073 --> 26:16.075
I know
it's in good hands.

26:16.075 --> 26:22.581
♪♪

26:22.581 --> 26:29.088
♪♪

26:31.090 --> 26:32.549
[ Glasses clink ]

26:32.549 --> 26:34.051
Margaret: Cheers.

26:34.051 --> 26:36.303
Only you all haven't signed the
Taste of Sonoma contracts yet,

26:36.303 --> 26:41.517
so is this a celebration
or a consolation prize?

26:41.517 --> 26:45.729
I'm sorry, Margaret, but we've
decided to change course.

26:45.729 --> 26:48.482
The Ritz
gave us a great deal.

26:48.482 --> 26:50.484
If this were about money,
you would have let me counter.

26:50.484 --> 26:52.945
You know this contract
isn't about dollars for me.

26:52.945 --> 26:55.405
This is about rebuilding
the Honeycroft name.

26:55.405 --> 26:57.574
We're sorry.
Our decision is final.

26:57.574 --> 27:00.536
Just curious.

27:00.536 --> 27:02.830
Does Joe keep your balls
in his pocket

27:02.830 --> 27:04.790
or in the humidor next
to your cigars?

27:04.790 --> 27:07.876
Now, Margaret, don't get
hysterical or bitchy about this.

27:07.876 --> 27:10.921
Oh, I never get hysterical
when it comes to business.

27:13.674 --> 27:16.593
Bitchy's another story.

27:19.972 --> 27:22.933
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:22.933 --> 27:24.560
Let me get you
another glass.

27:24.560 --> 27:26.186
I think it's gonna make it
easier to deal with them.

27:26.186 --> 27:27.437
Maybe bring the bottle.

27:27.437 --> 27:28.856
[ Chuckles ]

27:28.856 --> 27:31.775
♪♪

27:31.775 --> 27:34.945
♪ I was somewhere out west
in El Paso ♪

27:34.945 --> 27:37.656
♪ Or maybe it was Mexico ♪

27:37.656 --> 27:40.659
♪ With a brown‐eyed girl
in a mezcal world ♪

27:40.659 --> 27:42.578
♪ She was someone that
I didn't know ♪

27:42.578 --> 27:43.996
♪ I didn't, didn't,
didn't know ♪

27:43.996 --> 27:45.998
♪ Was headed for
a little vacation ♪

27:45.998 --> 27:48.876
I never get tired
of this view.

27:48.876 --> 27:52.796
Last year, some
Silicon Valley billionaire

27:52.796 --> 27:54.840
offered to buy
this place.

28:02.347 --> 28:04.433
♪ Sing a cowboy song ♪

28:04.433 --> 28:07.144
Allende is one of
my favorite writers.

28:07.144 --> 28:10.022
She's Chilean,
not Mexican,

28:10.022 --> 28:11.857
but we can't
all be perfect.

28:11.857 --> 28:12.983
[ Laughs ]

28:12.983 --> 28:14.735
♪ 'Cause my love is gone ♪

28:16.028 --> 28:17.613
Where are you from?

28:17.613 --> 28:19.072
El Salvador.

28:19.072 --> 28:20.157
Ah.

28:20.157 --> 28:22.200
I have always wanted
to go there.

28:22.200 --> 28:26.580
Most Americans think we're all,
you know, one culture.

28:26.580 --> 28:27.539
[ Groans ]

28:27.539 --> 28:28.665
"Your people."

28:28.665 --> 28:30.959
Mm. I know
what you mean.

28:30.959 --> 28:35.339
Still...there is something
that unites us.

28:40.510 --> 28:50.187
♪♪

28:50.187 --> 28:59.905
♪♪

28:59.905 --> 29:02.699
Hey. I need to talk
to you about something.

29:02.699 --> 29:05.535
In confidence.

29:05.535 --> 29:08.538
You're mad I didn't consult
with you before hiring Javier.

29:08.538 --> 29:11.667
Yes, but that's not
what I want to talk about.

29:11.667 --> 29:14.127
This is more important
than the company.

29:14.127 --> 29:16.672
Antonio and Javier
have a history.

29:16.672 --> 29:19.049
I have to ask,
did you know?

29:19.049 --> 29:23.095
Are you asking me
as Antonio's sister or as CEO?

29:23.095 --> 29:25.722
Does your answer change
depending on what I answer?

29:28.141 --> 29:29.643
Yes, I knew.

29:29.643 --> 29:30.978
For how long?

29:30.978 --> 29:34.272
Since I saw them kissing
near the Zin when they were 16.

29:37.359 --> 29:39.486
And you still
hired Javier,

29:39.486 --> 29:41.738
knowing how hard
that would be for Antonio.

29:41.738 --> 29:43.824
He's right.
You're just testing him.

29:45.117 --> 29:48.453
If Antonio can't put
the company above his feelings,

29:48.453 --> 29:53.458
then...he's not the man
I thought he was.

29:53.458 --> 29:56.211
That's the discipline,
Veronica.

29:56.211 --> 29:58.213
That's what it takes.

29:58.213 --> 30:00.507
From my first day
on the vineyard,

30:00.507 --> 30:03.010
there have been people
trying to tear me down,

30:03.010 --> 30:04.302
push me around.

30:04.302 --> 30:08.390
Yeah, but right now, the only
one tearing down my brother

30:08.390 --> 30:09.933
is you, Pa.

30:09.933 --> 30:13.603
So I'm asking you again,
are you here as Antonio's sister

30:13.603 --> 30:16.815
or as CEO
of Heritage House?

30:16.815 --> 30:18.275
Both.

30:18.275 --> 30:19.901
There may be times
when you have to choose

30:19.901 --> 30:22.362
one over the other.

30:22.362 --> 30:25.407
I'm sorry, Pa, but that's not
the leader I'm gonna be.

30:25.407 --> 30:27.826
Good luck with that.

30:29.786 --> 30:31.496
[ Cellphone chimes ]

30:31.496 --> 30:38.587
♪♪

30:38.587 --> 30:45.802
♪♪

30:54.227 --> 30:55.771
[ Sighs ]

31:08.366 --> 31:09.618
Buenos.

31:09.618 --> 31:11.078
Buenos.

31:11.078 --> 31:13.288
Um...
What have you heard?

31:13.288 --> 31:21.546
♪♪

31:27.469 --> 31:29.304
Thanks for
meeting me here.

31:30.889 --> 31:33.642
Sounded like you really
needed to see this place.

31:36.561 --> 31:38.105
Yeah.

31:39.856 --> 31:45.403
When I was at my worst,
strung out in the gutter,

31:45.403 --> 31:47.280
I dreamt about
this place.

31:50.492 --> 31:52.994
These vines
never leave you.

31:59.417 --> 32:02.045
Well, we had
some good times here.

32:02.045 --> 32:03.797
A few bad ones.

32:03.797 --> 32:05.549
But, you know,
as I get older,

32:05.549 --> 32:08.385
I just try to focus on
the happier days.

32:08.385 --> 32:10.971
Lettie.

32:10.971 --> 32:12.097
It won't be easy,

32:12.097 --> 32:14.141
but you need to tell Joe
I'm back.

32:17.310 --> 32:18.854
When the time is right.

32:18.854 --> 32:21.273
When is that?
What are you waiting for?

32:21.273 --> 32:23.275
What are you
waiting for?

32:26.069 --> 32:27.279
How's Junior?

32:27.279 --> 32:31.199
Oh, he's great...
thanks to you.

32:31.199 --> 32:33.785
Even his dad
notices a change.

32:35.162 --> 32:37.747
Notices a change in Junior
or a change in you?

32:37.747 --> 32:39.457
[ Laughs ]

32:40.792 --> 32:43.837
It was so much easier
to hate you when you were gone.

32:46.173 --> 32:48.175
How about now?

32:50.886 --> 32:54.806
[ Indistinct conversation
in Spanish in distance ]

33:22.167 --> 33:23.710
[ Speaks Spanish ]

33:33.094 --> 33:34.137
No, no, no.

33:42.729 --> 33:45.023
Lettie, Leticia.

33:54.282 --> 33:56.034
Gracias.

33:59.704 --> 34:01.373
Gracias.

34:15.595 --> 34:18.056
[ Sobbing ]

34:18.056 --> 34:19.849
[ Speaks Spanish ]

34:36.700 --> 34:37.784
Sí, Señor.

34:37.784 --> 34:40.620
[ Speaks Spanish ]

34:40.620 --> 34:46.543
♪♪

34:46.543 --> 34:52.549
♪♪

34:57.971 --> 35:00.015
Tell me what Mom
just told me isn't true.

35:00.015 --> 35:02.058
Your mother's at church,
so I assume you're talking about

35:02.058 --> 35:03.143
the woman who
gave birth to you.

35:03.143 --> 35:04.936
You sabotaged
the Taste of Sonoma.

35:04.936 --> 35:07.105
You took it away from Mom,
and you took it away from me.

35:07.105 --> 35:09.774
Your mom left when you were
2 years old.

35:09.774 --> 35:11.401
I think you
forgive too easily.

35:11.401 --> 35:12.986
I'm not like
Veronica or Antonio.

35:12.986 --> 35:15.280
I don't see things
black and white with my parents,

35:15.280 --> 35:17.032
and you should be grateful
that I don't.

35:17.032 --> 35:20.327
You get too close to Margaret,
she'll only hurt you again.

35:20.327 --> 35:22.912
You kept her away
so she wouldn't hurt me.

35:22.912 --> 35:24.998
You didn't consider the fact
that you might have

35:24.998 --> 35:27.626
also kept her away
from loving me.

35:31.880 --> 35:34.883
I'm sorry the project
didn't happen for you, mija,

35:34.883 --> 35:38.345
but I'm gonna
make it up to you.

35:38.345 --> 35:41.514
We've got a limited edition
release coming out.

35:41.514 --> 35:44.100
The bottle needs to
make a statement.

35:44.100 --> 35:47.437
Now, if
a Carmen Sandoval original

35:47.437 --> 35:50.106
doesn't make a statement,
then I don't know what will.

35:50.106 --> 35:51.274
Don't mess with me, Pa.

35:51.274 --> 35:53.485
Hey, you've got
a special talent, Carmen.

35:53.485 --> 35:55.320
I love your designs.

35:55.320 --> 35:58.490
What did you think
of that leopard design?

35:58.490 --> 36:00.158
Honestly?

36:00.158 --> 36:03.161
I think it's my favorite.
I love that one.

36:04.829 --> 36:07.165
I never did
a leopard design.

36:18.927 --> 36:21.471
That's only $10,000.

36:21.471 --> 36:23.306
What is this, huh?

36:23.306 --> 36:24.641
What is this?

36:24.641 --> 36:27.060
A retainer.

36:27.060 --> 36:28.228
Retainer?

36:28.228 --> 36:30.689
Look, I get it.

36:30.689 --> 36:32.774
You think
you can blow me up.

36:32.774 --> 36:35.443
But between my money,
my lawyers,

36:35.443 --> 36:40.073
my contacts at the
sheriff's department and ICE...

36:40.073 --> 36:42.033
I can do much worse.

36:43.326 --> 36:45.537
So why don't we help
each other instead?

36:45.537 --> 36:48.623
Find a mutually
beneficial arrangement.

36:48.623 --> 36:51.334
So what's this
retainer for?

36:51.334 --> 36:53.670
I want you
to follow my husband.

36:58.258 --> 37:00.468
Antonio: Yes, I understand.
Thank you.

37:00.468 --> 37:02.095
[ Beep ]

37:06.850 --> 37:10.270
The whispers your father
told us about the truck...

37:10.270 --> 37:12.313
the truth
might be worse.

37:12.313 --> 37:14.524
I asked a private investigator
to trace the VIN.

37:14.524 --> 37:18.069
The truck was stolen from
a house in Bakersfield in 1987,

37:18.069 --> 37:20.321
the same year
Joe and Lettie got here.

37:20.321 --> 37:21.531
And what?

37:21.531 --> 37:23.116
There was a murder
in that house.

37:23.116 --> 37:24.492
The police found
a man stabbed to death

37:24.492 --> 37:26.035
on the kitchen floor.

37:26.035 --> 37:27.871
You don't think
your father ‐‐
I don't know
what to think.

37:27.871 --> 37:30.123
My father has
a lot of enemies.

37:30.123 --> 37:33.042
People who'd love to connect him
to all kinds of nastiness.

37:33.042 --> 37:36.045
And who knows?
Maybe he is connected.

37:36.045 --> 37:38.298
But he's still
my father.

37:41.634 --> 37:44.137
And despite
everything he's done,

37:44.137 --> 37:48.975
despite...him
pushing me out...

37:51.686 --> 37:53.313
...I still love him.

37:55.690 --> 37:58.026
We're gonna
keep this quiet.

37:58.026 --> 37:59.068
I don't know about that,
Antonio.

37:59.068 --> 38:01.112
Javier, please.

38:03.490 --> 38:05.909
Can I trust you?

38:05.909 --> 38:08.036
Yeah.

38:08.036 --> 38:09.662
Thanks.

38:13.041 --> 38:14.876
Now get back to work.

38:17.086 --> 38:19.130
[ Chuckles ]

38:19.130 --> 38:28.890
♪♪

38:28.890 --> 38:29.891
[ Cellphone chimes ]

38:29.891 --> 38:34.437
♪♪

38:52.705 --> 38:54.415
[ Door closes, engine starts ]

39:05.718 --> 39:07.053
Sí.

39:07.053 --> 39:14.727
♪♪

39:14.727 --> 39:16.729
Polvorones.

39:18.356 --> 39:20.108
Now be honest,
did you make these,

39:20.108 --> 39:22.235
or did Marta?
[ Chuckles ]

39:22.235 --> 39:25.738
Well, it's my family recipe,
but you know Marta.

39:25.738 --> 39:27.198
It's her kitchen.

39:27.198 --> 39:29.200
She hasn't changed.

39:29.951 --> 39:31.369
Oye.

39:31.369 --> 39:33.580
Do you remember when she put
sugar instead of salt

39:33.580 --> 39:36.082
in the caldo because
we had complained

39:36.082 --> 39:38.501
that it didn't have
enough carrots?

39:38.501 --> 39:42.881
Foreman Gonzo accused her
of trying to poison us.

39:42.881 --> 39:44.632
[ Both laugh ]

39:46.759 --> 39:48.011
Hey, Dad.

39:48.011 --> 39:50.555
Hey, that's not the face
of the future Chivas head coach.

39:50.555 --> 39:52.515
Sorry,
I‐I just got a text.

39:52.515 --> 39:53.516
The kids
can't play tomorrow.

39:53.516 --> 39:54.767
The school only
has one van,

39:54.767 --> 39:56.519
and they're gonna use it
for the volleyball team.

39:56.519 --> 39:57.937
This means a lot to you.

39:57.937 --> 40:01.316
This priest,
he's really helped you out.

40:01.316 --> 40:03.568
Yeah, I was really
messed up, Dad.

40:03.568 --> 40:06.487
You're getting better.

40:06.487 --> 40:07.822
I'm trying to.

40:07.822 --> 40:10.742
I think we should try one

40:10.742 --> 40:12.410
to see if she's
trying to poison us.

40:12.410 --> 40:14.412
[ Laughs ] You go.

40:14.412 --> 40:15.914
You first.

40:15.914 --> 40:18.249
You go first.
You're going first.

40:18.249 --> 40:21.044
Hey, let's show
those kids how the Sandovals

40:21.044 --> 40:22.003
help their own.

40:22.003 --> 40:23.379
What?
Come on.

40:23.379 --> 40:25.131
For real?
Get in.

40:25.131 --> 40:26.215
[ Laughs ]

40:26.215 --> 40:31.012
♪♪

40:31.012 --> 40:32.430
Mm‐hmm.

40:32.430 --> 40:35.016
Mmm.

40:35.016 --> 40:36.225
Mm.

40:36.225 --> 40:38.144
You have something...

40:41.731 --> 40:43.858
Can't wait to see
the look on their faces.

40:43.858 --> 40:45.234
Go tell Father Ramos.

40:45.234 --> 40:46.736
He should hear
the good news from you.

40:46.736 --> 40:48.529
No, why don't we, uh,
go in together?

40:48.529 --> 40:50.239
It's your gift, too.

40:50.239 --> 40:51.616
Okay.

40:53.409 --> 40:54.577
[ Door opens ]

40:54.577 --> 40:56.496
Yeah, so I have
the soccer balls in the back.

40:56.496 --> 40:58.957
[ Speaks
indistinctly ]

40:58.957 --> 40:59.958
[ Lettie laughs ]

40:59.958 --> 41:02.585
[ Indistinct conversation ]

41:02.585 --> 41:07.465
♪♪

41:07.465 --> 41:08.591
Lettie?

41:08.591 --> 41:14.263
♪♪

41:14.263 --> 41:19.978
♪♪

41:23.856 --> 41:26.567
♪♪

41:26.567 --> 41:27.986
Billy.

41:30.321 --> 41:32.115
Hello, brother.

41:32.115 --> 41:36.619
♪♪

